place.name: TREMAINE
place.gazetteerText: TREMAYNE, a parish in Launceston district, Cornwall; 6½ miles WNW of Launceston r. station. Post town, Launceston. Acres, 1,045. Real property, £628. Pop., 109. Houses, 22. The living is annexed to Egloskerry. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
